SIMPLE: trier
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trier
<hw>Tri"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Try</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who tries; one who makes
experiments; one who examines anything by a test or standard.</def>
<rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who tries judicially.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A person appointed according to law
to try challenges of jurors; a trior.</def>
<rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>That which tries or approves; a test.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trierarch</ent>⟦br⟧
